  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We discuss the (fine) level structure suggested by the membrane approach to quantum black holes. We study the small fluctuations of a membrane close to the event horizon, examine the relation between energy levels and entropy, and find corrections to the $A/4$ term proportional to $\log M$ (for Schwarzschild black holes). We finally relate this results with previous work on critical phenomena in black hole thermodynamics.</subfield>
